laboratory_examinations.findings: An 11 mm hypodense lesion at the periphery of the left lobe of the liver. No additional focal hepatic abnormality identified. Hypoattenuating lesions within the kidneys bilaterally most likely represent cysts. Wall thickening and surrounding fat stranding in the segment of descending colon measuring approximately 10 cm. Colonic diverticulae present. A 2.4 cm hyperattenuating mass within the fundus of the uterus likely represents a fibroid.
